# English-only code comments (no Chinese)

For **all new and edited code** in this repository, **comments must be written in English only**. Do not add Chinese (or other non-English) text in comments.

Works with `english-comments-and-logs.mdc` (logs also English) and `function-documentation.mdc` (JSDoc in English).

## Applies to

- `//` line comments and trailing inline comments
- `/** */` JSDoc and block comments
- CSS/SCSS `/* */` comments
- JSX `{/* */}` comments

## Does not apply to

- User-facing copy in `public/_locales/**` (i18n messages)
- Locale display labels (e.g. `zh_CN: 'Chinese'`)
- Runtime error/log strings in untouched legacy code (refactor to English when you touch that code)

## When editing legacy files

- **New or changed comments** → English
- **Functions you touch** without docs → add English JSDoc (see `function-documentation.mdc`)
- Do **not** bulk-replace Chinese in unrelated legacy strings unless the user asks

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ English comment
/** Fetch HLS playlist text before resume to refresh signed segment URLs. */
async function fetchM3u8TextForResume(): Promise<string> {}

// ❌ Non-English comment — do not add
// [fetch m3u8 before resume — wrong language]
/** [non-English JSDoc] */
```

```css
/* ✅ Download queue section layout */
/* ❌ Non-English CSS comment */
```

```tsx
{/* ✅ Download queue section */}
{/* ❌ Non-English JSX comment */}
```
